TY  - JOUR
T1  - Optimal Advertising with Stochastic Demand
AU  - Monahan, George E.
Y1  - 1983/01/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.29.1.106
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.29.1.106
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 106
EP  - 117
VL  - 29
IS  - 1
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A stochastic, sequential model is developed to determine optimal advertising expenditures as a function of product maturity and past advertising. Random demand for the product depends upon an aggregate measure of current and past advertising called ?goodwill,? and the position of the product in its life cycle measured by sales-to-date. Conditions on the parameters of the model are established that insure that it is optimal to advertise less as the product matures. Additional characteristics of the optimal advertising policy are also established.
AB  - A stochastic, sequential model is developed to determine optimal advertising expenditures as a function of product maturity and past advertising. Random demand for the product depends upon an aggregate measure of current and past advertising called ?goodwill,? and the position of the product in its life cycle measured by sales-to-date. Conditions on the parameters of the model are established that insure that it is optimal to advertise less as the product matures. Additional characteristics of the optimal advertising policy are also established.
